          "End of Course",
          "Authors do a different approach as they intend to explore the idea of fairness. \n\nAnalysis of results takes into account multi-group fairness - how distributions of certain attributes may affect the “predictions” and performance of a model. \n\nThis fairness evoluations is conducted by the selection of an approppriate metric, ",
          "kNN, SVM, Gaussian Naive Bayes, Logistic Regression, MLP ",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{Macro-BPSN AUC: 0.9359}",
          "Authors do a standard ML pipeline where not only do they solve a regular classification problem but afterward try to do an analysis of Bias using BPSN. \n\nThis analysis is subsequently confirmed with a Reinforcement Learning approach.",
          "Specific to an Algebra Context.\n\nNO XAI analysis."
        ]
